dc:title: Goshen Springs: late Quaternary vegetation record for southern Alabama.
dc:creator: Delcourt P.
dc:description: The sediments of Goshen Springs, Pike County, Alabama, provide a late Quaternary biostratigraphic record that extends from the Altonian Substage of the Wisconsinan to the present. Diagrams showing percentages of palynomorphs and concentrations of plant macrofossils permit the reconstruction of both local and regional vegetation. -from AuthorPike County (Alabama) Altonian Substage biostratigraphic record
